 kinase is markedly elevated in the absence of strenuous exercise or if myopathy is otherwise suspected or diagnosed.', 'Metabolism', 'Concomitant use of ticagrelor with simvastatin or lovastatin dosages above 40 mg/day is not recommended.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/166168/', '', 'Glipizide, Acetohexamide, Guar gum, Pramlintide, Alogliptin, Rosuvastatin, Tolazamide, Empagliflozin, Dulaglutide, Exenatide, Tolbutamide, More', 'Betrixaban, Apixaban, Cilostazol, Rivaroxaban, Lepirudin, Urokinase, Cangrelor, Caplacizumab, Argatroban, Prasugrel, Desirudin, More', 1767369485);
